Workflow Trigger (Commit / Schedule / Manual / Storefront / Onboarding)
 ├─ Contributor Onboarding (Atomic Drop)
 ├─ Storefront Bundles (Mustang, Mercedes SL, Maadi rifle, Ammo)
 ├─ Talent Intake Flow
 ├─ Deploy Static Content / Pages / Theme
 ├─ Deploy Signal System
 ├─ Seal Scroll
 ├─ Route GitHub Notification → OracleSignal
 ├─ Sitemap Deploy
 └─ Crypto Oracle 24-Hour Loop

Step 1: Initial Run
 └─ Execute workflow or bundle action
     → Success → Audit Log + Legacy Broadcast
     → Failure → Route to Recovery Path

Step 2: Recovery Path (on Failure)
 ├─ Collect Logs
 │   → Capture runner output, bureau responses, error codes
 │   → Store in immutable audit vault
 ├─ Validate Environment
 │   → Check secrets, tokens, API endpoints
 │   → Verify dependencies (Node.js, bureau API, Shopify, OracleSignal)
 ├─ Retry Logic
 │   → Exponential backoff retry (up to N attempts)
 │   → If still failing → escalate
 ├─ Incident Creation
 │   → POST /incident/create with runId + bundle ID + error snapshot
 │   → Notify OracleSignal + Dashboard alert
 └─ Rollback / Quarantine
     → Revert to last good artifact (Pages, Sitemap, Theme)
     → Quarantine bad storefront bundle (Mustang, SL, Maadi, Ammo)
     → Require manual override for sensitive contributor actions

Step 3: Dashboard Visibility
 ├─ Contributor feeds (onboarding compliance, fraud alerts)
 ├─ Storefront feeds (bundle status, disputes, approvals)
 ├─ Workflow feeds (success/failure, retries, incidents)
 ├─ Signal streams (GitHub commits, OracleSignal routes)
 └─ Oracle feeds (crypto loop outputs, health checks)

Step 4: Legacy Locking
 ├─ Snapshot: contributor/bundle result + artifact hash + bureau response
 ├─ Store: immutable audit vault (append-only)
 └─ Broadcast: /legacy/broadcast → public proof stream
